column2: I used to work in a shelter for abused men. I am well aware of this travesty.
column22: Donna Brazile was fired from CNM for handing Hillary debate questions and rewarded by appointment to DNC Chair. This splits the Democratic Party even more than it was split, before.
column52: I feel that Johnny Depp deserves justice after being disrespected during the whole Amber Heard abuse allagations.   He was fired from films and had awful things said about him,when HE was the victim.  Men are subject to Domestic abuse/violence and they don't talk about it while being accused of the abuse.  Men deserve equality where any type of abuse is occuring.   Society so often is quick to console the woman and discount the man on the 'assumption' that only the man can be physically abusive/violent.    Not just for Johnny,but for ALL men who suffer in silence at the hand of an abusive woman.   Not only physically,but there is also emotional,mental and verbal abuse.   All of it is WRONG and I feel that Amber Heard should recieve the same treatment as a man would have gotten.   "Equality" means equal:50/50...If women need a voice to speak out against Domestic Abuse,men need one as well.   Stop assuming everything is the fault of the man,and start looking into the women.  Things are not always as they appear.

column2: I believe Johnny, even with his faults (that all of us also have), is a genuinely good, stand up guy. I lived with a narcissist for a long time.
